-- BMW and Toyota Agree on Expanding Cooperation, Der Spiegel Says
-- B y   T o n y   C z u c z k a
-- 2012-06-24T10:13:46Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-06-24/bmw-and-toyota-agree-on-expanding-cooperation-der-spiegel-says.html
Bayerische Motoren Werke AG (BMW)  and
 Toyota Motor Corp. (7203)  have agreed on several joint projects,
expanding their cooperation,  Der Spiegel   reported , without
saying how it got the information.  An announcement on the projects is expected soon, the
German magazine said in an e-mailed preview of an article for
its latest edition.  BMW can benefit from Toyota’s experience in hybrids, fuel
cells and automotive electronics, while Toyota can benefit from
BMW’s experience in light materials, Der Spiegel said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Tony Czuczka in Berlin at 
 aczuczka@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
James Hertling at 
 jhertling@bloomberg.net  